    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of architecture developed during the Song dynasty (970-1279 BCE) in China and introduced into Japan along with Zen Buddhism during the Kamakura period (1185-1333). The style is characterized by smaller, more structurally complex buildings than before, with strongly articulated bracketing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de la arquitectura desarrollado durante la dinastía Sung (970-1279 BCE) en China e introducido en Japón junto con el budismo Zen durante el período de Kamakura (1185-1333). El estilo es caracterizado por se más pequeño, edificios estructuralmente mas complejos que antes, fuertemente articulado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de architectuurstijl die zich ontwikkelde tijdens de Song dynastie (970-1279 v. Chr.) in China en die tijdens de Kamakura periode (1185-1333) samen met het Zen-Boeddhisme in Japan werd geïntroduceerd. De stijl kenmerkt zich door kleinere, complexere gebouwen met zeer nadrukkelijke consoles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指發展於中國宋代（西元970年至1279年），鐮倉時期（西元1185年至1333年）與襌宗佛教一起引進日本的建築風格。此風格的建築體積較之前的小，結構較為複雜，有堅固的托座。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
